---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const lang = 'en';
const pageTitle = 'Case studies - Alexis Fiska';
const pageDescription =
  'Explore three case studies showing how my services helped Ornikar, Xpollens and GenAI projects improve software quality and speed up releases.';
---
<BaseLayout lang={lang} title={pageTitle} description={pageDescription}>
  <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6 text-center">Case studies</h1>
  <p class="max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-10 text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300 text-center">
    Every project is unique. Here is how I helped clients from different sectors achieve effective
    and sustainable test automation. Exact figures are intentionally omitted or anonymised in
    accordance with non‑disclosure agreements.
  </p>

  <article class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-2 text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400">Ornikar</h2>
    <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mt-4 mb-1">Context</h3>
    <p class="mb-3 text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300">
      Online driving school platform in hypergrowth requiring increased E2E reliability to support
      expansion and secure training and payment journeys.
    </p>
    <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mt-4 mb-1">Objectives</h3>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mb-3 text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300 space-y-1">
      <li>Reduce test execution time and improve stability.</li>
      <li>Implement a BDD framework with SpecFlow suitable for the .NET team.</li>
      <li>Automate critical journeys (registration, booking, payment).</li>
    </ul>
    <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mt-4 mb-1">Approach</h3>
    <p class="mb-3 text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300">
      Following a pipeline audit, I designed a Playwright + SpecFlow framework using the Page Object
      pattern. Tests were parallelised and integrated into GitHub Actions with clear reporting. The
      internal developers and QA received training.
    </p>
    <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mt-4 mb-1">Results</h3>
    <p class="mb-3 text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300">
      Execution times dropped below 20 minutes with coverage of 80 % of critical journeys. Regression
      bugs decreased and the team now has a reliable, maintainable pipeline.
    </p>
    <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mt-4 mb-1">Stack</h3>
    <p class="mb-3 text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300">
      Playwright, SpecFlow (.NET), GitHub Actions, Azure DevOps.
    </p>
    <p class="text-xs italic text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-400">
      Exact figures and results are covered by a confidentiality agreement.
    </p>
  </article>

  <article class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-2 text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400">Xpollens</h2>
    <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mt-4 mb-1">Context</h3>
    <p class="mb-3 text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300">
      FinTech providing payment and card APIs with strong regulatory constraints and a high release
      cadence. Quality and compliance are essential.
    </p>
    <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mt-4 mb-1">Objectives</h3>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mb-3 text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300 space-y-1">
      <li>Establish reliable contract and UI tests.</li>
      <li>Fit naturally into the existing CI/CD pipeline under GitLab.</li>
      <li>Train the internal team to maintain the tests.</li>
    </ul>
    <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mt-4 mb-1">Approach</h3>
    <p class="mb-3 text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300">
      I built a suite of API tests using Postman/Newman and BDD UI scenarios. Continuous integration
      under GitLab CI with parallelisation and reporting was deployed. Training workshops strengthened
      team autonomy.
    </p>
    <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mt-4 mb-1">Results</h3>
    <p class="mb-3 text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300">
      Production bugs were halved, enabling calmer weekly releases. The QA team is now autonomous in
      maintaining and evolving the framework.
    </p>
    <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mt-4 mb-1">Stack</h3>
    <p class="mb-3 text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300">
      Playwright, Postman/Newman, GitLab CI, Kubernetes.
    </p>
    <p class="text-xs italic text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-400">
      Exact figures and results are covered by a confidentiality agreement.
    </p>
  </article>

  <article class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-2 text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400">GenAI projects</h2>
    <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mt-4 mb-1">Context</h3>
    <p class="mb-3 text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300">
      Experiments exploring the use of generative models to assist QA in data generation and log
      analysis. The results serve to explore new, innovative approaches.
    </p>
    <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mt-4 mb-1">Objectives</h3>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mb-3 text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300 space-y-1">
      <li>Generate diverse, realistic synthetic data sets.</li>
      <li>Automatically analyse logs to detect anomalies and suggest tests.</li>
      <li>Measure the impact of these tools on QA team productivity.</li>
    </ul>
    <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mt-4 mb-1">Approach</h3>
    <p class="mb-3 text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300">
      Open‑source models and language APIs were integrated via Python scripts and LangChain. Qualitative
      and quantitative evaluations compared generated datasets and test suggestions.
    </p>
    <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mt-4 mb-1">Results</h3>
    <p class="mb-3 text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300">
      The proofs of concept showed significant productivity gains, reducing test writing time and
      proposing new coverage ideas. Progressive adoption is underway.
    </p>
    <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mt-4 mb-1">Stack</h3>
    <p class="mb-3 text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300">
      Python, LangChain, OpenAI API / open‑source models.
    </p>
    <p class="text-xs italic text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-400">
      Exact figures and results are covered by a confidentiality agreement.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>